ly approaches is encouraged, with the governing criterion being simply that the work is of interest to an international audience"--cProvided by publisher.  a4410aKelsen, Hans,d1881-1973xCorrespondence.10aSchmitt, Carl,d1888-1985xCorrespondence. 0aConstitutional lawxPhilosophy. 0aExecutive powerzGermany.1 aKelsen, Hans,d1881-1973,eauthor.1 aSchmitt, Carl,d1888-1985,eauthor.1 aVinx, Lars,eeditoretranslator 0aCambridge studies in constitutional law ;vno. 12.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://dx.doi.org/10.1017/CBO9781316136256  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6800014-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu2/9/2015xE-BOOKzCBO01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2007041211bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/36367193